author: Bay Area News Group
title: Local sports digest: Stanford swim star Manuel to redshirt 2015-16 season
text:
Local sports digest: Stanford swim star Manuel to redshirt 2015-16 season Bay Area News Group Posted: 10/22/2015 08:04:56 PM PDT Updated: 10/22/2015 11:41:07 PM PDT Stanford's Simone Manuel is taking a year off from collegiate swimming to prepare for the 2016 Summer Olympics, Cardinal coach Greg Meehan announced Thursday. 
Manuel gained national attention in the spring when she and Stanford teammate Lia Neal and Florida's Natalie Hinds became the first African-Americans to take the top three spots in a race at the NCAA championships. They finished first through third in the 100-yard sprint. 
Haley Rosen had a goal and an assist, and Averie Collins scored in the 109th minute to lift the No. 4 Stanford women's soccer team to a 2-1 double-overtime victory at No. 25 Washington State. 
Second-half goals from Grace Cutler and Julie Vass gave the No. 20 Santa Clara women's soccer team a 2-1 win over San Diego. 
Saint Mary's hit only 19.3 percent in a 3-0 women's volleyball loss at USF. 
Nikki Hess had 19 kills and 13 digs as Santa Clara beat Pacific 3-2 in women's volleyball. 
Giulia Gavio had 15 kills and Yavianliz Rosado had 19 digs, but San Jose State (11-11, 3-6 Mountain West) lost 3-1 at home to UNLV in women's volleyball. 
Saint Mary's Manuel De Luis Lamales and Nash Vollenweider defeated Cal's Gunther Matta and Ryan Shen 8-5 in the main doubles draw at the USTA/ITA Northwest Regional Championships in Seattle. 
Santa Clara's Owen Asalone and DeMarco Orella scored a minute apart in the fourth quarter as host Santa Clara (6-14) rallied to beat Cal Baptist 9-8 in men's water polo. Advertisement 
No. 4 Pacific beat host San Jose State (3-16, 0-4 MPSF) 16-6 in men's water polo. Alek Dendall scored three goals for the Spartans. MMA San Jose is scheduled to host a mixed martial arts card Dec. 4 at the San Jose State Event Center, featuring Josh Thomson in the main event. Figure skating Fremont teen Karen Chen opens the International Grand Prix season this weekend at Skate America in Milwaukee. Chen, 16, joins Olympian Gracie Gold and Mariah Bell in the women's competition.
